ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes! Take it! But only if you have good reasons to do so. If you don't like French, medieval studies, or translation, you aren't going to enjoy it. If you like any of those three, it's a wonderful course!
See responses above. Yes, would highly recommend.
This course is perfect for students interested in learning how to read old French and who want to do so by working closely with La Mort Artu, a fascinating text in the Lancelot Prose Cycle.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Old French will be an important part of my future research into the secular visual culture of late medieval Europe.
The skills that I acquired in this course have given me access to a wide range of texts available only in old French.
